# Anti-AI Patterns (What NOT to Do)

Reference: `.mba-template/anti-patterns/ai-generated-tells.md`

## Visual Red Flags

### ❌ 1. Excessive Gradients
**Never:**
- Gradients on every element
- Rainbow gradients without purpose
- Multiple gradient directions
- Gradients on text (hard to read)

**Instead:**
- Use gradients sparingly (hero, CTA only)
- Subtle, purposeful gradients
- Consistent direction
- Solid colors for text

### ❌ 2. Over-Rounded Corners
**Never:**
- Border radius > 16px on small elements
- Mixing 8px, 12px, 15px, 20px randomly
- Circular buttons for non-icon buttons

**Instead:**
- Consistent radius scale (4px, 8px, 12px, 16px)
- 4-8px for buttons/inputs
- 8-12px for cards
- Maximum 16px (except pills/avatars)

### ❌ 3. Random Spacing
**Never:**
- 7px, 13px, 19px, 23px spacing
- No consistent scale
- Arbitrary pixel values

**Instead:**
- 4px or 8px base unit
- Consistent scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48)
- Same spacing for same hierarchy

### ❌ 4. Low Contrast Text
**Never:**
- #999 on #FFF (3:1 ratio)
- Light gray on white
- Colored text without checking contrast

**Instead:**
- WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1)
- #171717, #525252, #737373 on white
- Test with contrast checker

### ❌ 5. Generic Placeholders
**Never:**
- "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet..."
- "Click here" buttons
- "Product Name" as title
- "John Doe" everywhere

**Instead:**
- "Acme Analytics Dashboard"
- "View detailed report" buttons
- "Enterprise Analytics Pro"
- Diverse, realistic names

## Layout Red Flags

### ❌ 6. Centered Everything
**Never:**
- All text centered
- Form labels centered
- Buttons centered in cards

**Instead:**
- Left-align text for readability
- Right-align numbers/dates
- Center only hero sections, modals

### ❌ 7. Inconsistent Sizing
**Never:**
- Buttons: 34px, 38px, 42px randomly
- Icons: 18px, 24px, 28px mixed
- No size system

**Instead:**
- Defined sizes: small (32px), medium (40px), large (48px)
- Icon sizes: 16px, 20px, 24px
- Consistent throughout

### ❌ 8. No Visual Hierarchy
**Never:**
- All text same size
- No weight variation
- Everything equally prominent

**Instead:**
- Clear heading sizes (H1 > H2 > H3)
- Weight for emphasis (regular, semibold, bold)
- Primary/secondary action distinction

## Color Red Flags

### ❌ 9. Rainbow Colors
**Never:**
- Using 8+ colors
- Random color assignments
- Bright colors everywhere

**Instead:**
- 2-3 accent colors maximum
- Semantic colors (red=error, green=success)
- Neutral base with color accents

### ❌ 10. Inconsistent Color Usage
**Never:**
- Primary button blue then green
- Error messages in different reds
- Links in multiple colors

**Instead:**
- Consistent primary color
- Same semantic colors throughout
- Defined color roles

## Typography Red Flags

### ❌ 11. Too Many Fonts
**Never:**
- 3+ font families
- Decorative fonts for body
- Script fonts for UI

**Instead:**
- 1-2 font families maximum
- Sans-serif for UI
- Clear type scale

### ❌ 12. Poor Line Length
**Never:**
- Text spanning full width (150+ chars)
- Very short lines (20-30 chars)

**Instead:**
- 50-75 characters per line
- max-width: 65ch
- Comfortable reading

## Interaction Red Flags

### ❌ 13. No Hover/Focus States
**Never:**
- Buttons same on hover
- No focus indicators
- No visual feedback

**Instead:**
- Clear hover states
- 2px focus outlines
- Active states for buttons

### ❌ 14. Tiny Touch Targets
**Never:**
- Buttons < 32px
- Links too close
- Mobile UI with desktop sizing

**Instead:**
- 44px × 44px minimum (touch)
- Adequate spacing (8px+)
- Larger targets on mobile

## Content Red Flags

### ❌ 15. Unrealistic Data
**Never:**
- All values 100, 200, 300
- Perfect round numbers
- All dates same day

**Instead:**
- Realistic, varied numbers
- Mixed decimals ($1,234.56)
- Varied dates and times

### ❌ 16. No Empty/Error States
**Never:**
- Tables always full
- No error handling
- Perfect scenarios only

**Instead:**
- Empty state designs
- Error messages
- Loading indicators

## Professional Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

### Spacing
- [ ] Uses consistent scale (no 7px, 13px, 19px)
- [ ] Same spacing for same hierarchy
- [ ] Mathematically related values

### Colors
- [ ] Limited palette (6-7 families max)
- [ ] Semantic meaning
- [ ] WCAG AA contrast
- [ ] Consistent usage

### Typography
- [ ] 1-2 font families
- [ ] Clear hierarchy
- [ ] Readable line length
- [ ] Sufficient size (14px+ body)

### Layout
- [ ] Left-aligned text (mostly)
- [ ] Consistent component sizing
- [ ] Clear visual hierarchy
- [ ] Proper whitespace

### Interaction
- [ ] Hover states
- [ ] Focus indicators (2px)
- [ ] Touch targets (44px+)
- [ ] Keyboard navigation

### Content
- [ ] Realistic data
- [ ] Varied numbers/dates
- [ ] Meaningful text
- [ ] Empty/error states

## Quick Test

Ask yourself:
1. **Could a human designer have made this?**
2. **Does it follow a consistent system?**
3. **Is everything intentional?**
4. **Does it look like a real product?**
5. **Would users trust this interface?**

If any answer is "no", revise.

## Common AI Tells Summary

**Visual:**
- Too many gradients
- Over-rounded corners
- Random spacing
- Low contrast

**Layout:**
- Everything centered
- Inconsistent sizing
- No hierarchy

**Color:**
- Rainbow palette
- Inconsistent usage

**Typography:**
- Too many fonts
- Poor line length

**Interaction:**
- No states
- Tiny targets

**Content:**
- Lorem ipsum
- Perfect data
- No edge cases

## Professional Standards

**Always:**
- Consistent spacing scale
- Limited color palette
- Clear hierarchy
- Semantic HTML
- Real content
- Accessible design
- Platform patterns
- Internal consistency

**Never:**
- Random values
- Excessive decoration
- Generic placeholders
- Ignore accessibility
- Skip edge cases
- Reinvent patterns
- Over-design

